Acknowledgement: - 

 

First of all, I am grateful to the School of Technology (SOT), Director SOT- Prof. Sunil Khanna, CSSI Coordinator SOT- Dr. Poonam Mishra and Dr. Meera Karamta, CSSI Coordinator EC branch-Dr. Pradip Barik for successfully arranging the civic and social internship program for us. 

 

The internship opportunity I had with Sai Roti Sewa Sangh was a great chance for learning and social development. I would like to express my special thanks of gratitude to the Chairperson of the Organization, Mr. Dollar Bhai Adalja and Mr. Ramesh Bhai Patel and also an important Committee member Mr. Dharmesh Bhai Shah, who in spite of being extraordinarily busy with their work took time out to hear, guide and keep me on the right path during the entire internship program. 

 

Also, I express my deepest sense of gratitude to my family and friends without whose help and support this internship wouldn't have been successful. 

 

Above all, I would like to thank God Almighty for giving me the strength, knowledge, ability, and opportunity to undertake this internship for uplifting the lifestyle of poor people and understanding our social culture.

ABSTRACT: - 

 

FOOD DISTRIBUTION  

 

To help the needy patients and poor in the locality and understand their hardships I underwent my CSSI Internship at the Organization of Sai Roti Sewa Sangh, a Charitable Trust made for the poor section of the society. I spent 10 days of my vacation to help them out and spread some Happiness along with gaining much more. I came to know about the problems that they faced in their day-to-day life. 

 

The organization plays a wonderful role in serving the needs of people, helping patients and resolving the problem of food availability to the ones who either cannot afford it or are in need of it at the moment. They collect money from the traders and businessman of the city and surroundings who can provide help and provide food to the people in Hospitals every day to anyone who comes there whether they are patients or poor. They spend their time and money for others help and are doing this for years daily for the ones who don’t have adequate facilities. 

 

I think that what they are doing is what society needs at the moment and they are doing it willingly as they know that they have got the resources and reach to help someone out and consider it their responsibility instead of thinking it as a social work for the welfare of people. That is what I learned and will try to implement in my future life. 

 

But they need recognition because there are more people out there willing to provide their time and money to this but they don’t know about this Initiative so the govt. must help them out and recognize these type of local organizations because at present they are working at a comparatively small scale than they can work at if they get help.
